# HASHCAT
Nixpkgs: nixpkgs.hashcat
Source: https://github.com/hashcat/hashcat
Description: World's fastest and most advanced password recovery utility.
Version: hashcat --version

## Commands

### Basics
- hashcat -m 0 hash.txt wordlist.txt: Crack MD5 hashes using a wordlist.

### Essentials
- hashcat -a 3 -m 0 hash.txt ?a?a?a?a: Brute-force 4-character MD5.
- hashcat --benchmark: Run hardware benchmark.

### Intermediaries
- hashcat -m 1800 shadow.txt wordlist.txt: Crack Linux SHA-512 hashes.
- hashcat -m 0 hash.txt wordlist.txt -r rules/best64.rule: Apply rules to wordlist.

### Advanceds
- hashcat -a 1 -m 0 hash.txt list1.txt list2.txt: Combinator attack (join two wordlists).

### Uncommons
- hashcat --stdout -r rules/best64.rule wordlist.txt: Preview rule transformations without cracking.

## Tips
- Use -w 3 or -w 4 for high performance if the machine is dedicated.

## Disclaimers
- High power usage and heat generation. Ensure adequate cooling for GPU.

## Alternatives
- john: John the Ripper (better for CPU-based/heuristic attacks).

